            "headline": "Universitätsprofessor an der Humboldt-Universität zu Berlin",
            "summary": "Thomas Hoffmann studied sociology, psychology and political science at the Universities of Hamburg and Berlin. Practical experience as an adult educator in homes, day centers and sheltered workshops for people with severe and multiple handicaps. Adjunct professor and research fellow at the Universities of Hamburg, Cologne, and Ludwigsburg. Since 2007, assistant professor (german: Akademischer Oberrat) at the Department of Special Education at Ludwigsburg University of Education. 2011 Doctor of Education. 2015-2016 visiting professor at the Department of Special Education at Heidelberg University of Education and 2016-2017 visiting professor at the Department of Rehabilitation Sciences of the Humboldt-Universität zu Berlin. 2018-2024 Professor for Inclusive Education at the University of Innsbruck. Since 2024 Professor at the Department of Rehabilitation Sciences of the Humboldt-Universität zu Berlin.",
